## Cron Setup (External Cron — NOT Vercel Crons)

The app uses **external cron-jobs** (e.g. cron-job.org), not Vercel's built-in crons.

Call these URLs with header `X-Cron-Secret: <CRON_SECRET>`:

| Endpoint | Typical interval | What it does |
|----------|------------------|--------------|
| `/api/cron/dm-first-welcome` | Every **1 to 2 min** | First incoming auto-DM sweep (Instagram, Facebook, X); returns **202** and finishes in `after()` |
| `/api/cron/process-scheduled` | Every **5 min** | Due scheduled publishes (and email-link sends); keep tight for a 5-minute publish window |
| `/api/cron/comment-automation` | Every **5 min** | Keyword comment automation |
| `/api/cron/sync-platform-data` | Every **30 min** | Account overview + post discovery + post metrics (heavy Meta usage: do not run this every 5 min) |
| `/api/cron/metric-snapshots` | Daily | Follower or fan daily snapshot (Instagram + Facebook) |
| `/api/cron/sync-linkedin` | Every **30 min** | LinkedIn rollup (if you use LinkedIn) |

**Copy-paste schedule:** see **`docs/CRON_SCHEDULES.md`**.

**HTTP note:** Most cron handlers run **inline** and return JSON when finished. **`/api/cron/dm-first-welcome`** returns **202** immediately and finishes work in **`after()`** (like some publish routes), so a short client timeout still accepts the job. cron-job.org free tier often caps the client wait at **30s**; if a run times out on the client, the work may still complete server-side. Tune `CRON_SYNC_HTTP_BUDGET_MS`, **`DM_FIRST_WELCOME_SWEEP_BUDGET_MS`**, and automation budgets in code or env. Optional: cron-job.org paid tiers allow longer timeouts.

**Inbox comments** load when users open Inbox. **First incoming auto-DM** uses the same send rules as Inbox and is also driven by **`/api/cron/dm-first-welcome`** (every one to two minutes) so replies can go out in the background.

