## Stale Thresholds (summary)

Source of truth: `src/lib/sync/config.ts` (`STALE_THRESHOLDS`). Approximate:

| Platform | account_overview | posts | post_metrics | comments / messages |
|----------|------------------|-------|--------------|---------------------|
| Instagram / Facebook | 12 h | 4 h | 24 h | 30 min |
| TikTok | 12 h | 60 min | 6 h | 30 min |
| YouTube | 12 h | 60 min | 6 h | 30 min |
| X (Twitter) | 6 h | 30 min | 12 h | 30 min |

Scheduled `comments` and `messages` scopes exist for the sync engine, but Instagram and Facebook adapters do not yet pull inbox threads into the DB on cron (inbox uses live API routes).
